RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 73. Allowance Purse 8000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON THREE RACES. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. (Races at OR Fairs or WA Class C Tracks Not Considered in Eligibility).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: QUEENSBORO stalked the pace early, made a run outside rivals to take the lead nearing the second turn then pushed away and held under steady urging. SUE GENEROUS dueled for the lead from the rail, was overtaken by the winner then dug in late to hold the place. GET MY POINT tracked the pace from the rail to the stretch then could not make an impact. DATQUICKCAT had no speed, trailed for a half mile then could only pick off rivals. GOOD JOB JACKIE was outsprinted to the backstretch, tried to respond two deep but came up empty. SHE HAD A SECRET had no speed and was never a threat. HEY WILMAAA dueled for the lead for a half mile then tired.

ENTRY.NAME: Get My Point
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked pace, saved ground, no threat

ENTRY.NAME: Queensboro
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace, bid 3/8s, rallied to lead, clear driving

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 2 400 Y Dirt CR: 73. Maiden Purse 6000. FOR MAIDENS, TWO YEARS OLD. Weight, 125 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CPR A AMERICAN EAGLE broke out, straightened, strong run. ONE PAINTED ROAD steady urging. PARVEYOR bumped start, willingly. BELLEZA DIVINA chased throughout. SHEZA SPECIAL TRICK broke out, bumped foe. CPR MYFAVORITEWAGON bumped start, outrun. MISS SPECIAL TRAITS bobbled start, bumped.

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 3 6F Dirt CR: 82. Claiming Purse 8000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $6,250. Oregon Bred Claiming Price $8,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: RED NOON RISING was on a three horse duel to the backstretch, inched away from the runner up on the second turn and held driving. MS PARKSIDE attended the pace three wide, got outkicked on the second turn then was no threat in the lane. BETE ROUGE had brief speed, dropped back to last on the backstretch then tripped over the fallen horse on the second turn and fell. QUEEN BREEZY trailed to the backstretch, went by BETE ROUGE to chase the top two but suffered an injury on the second turn and was vanned off. A stewards inquiry into the accident did not alter the results.

ENTRY.NAME: Bete Rouge
ENTRY.COMMENT: brief speed, dropped back, fell 2d turn

ENTRY.NAME: Queen Breezy
ENTRY.OWNER: Carmody Jerry Sutton Ronald B and Duke Dave
ENTRY.COMMENT: trailed, pushed up, injured 2d turn, vanned off

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 4 400 Y Dirt CR: 85. Allowance Purse 8500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: JESSTAFIABLY JESS good late rally. MESSANGER hustled, led late, tagged. BV MARY ROSE dueled, dug in gamely. RADAR no speed, came on. NEWPORT GUY lugged out. GOOD JESS CARTEL no factor. CUTE GURL no speed.

ENTRY.NAME: Newport Guy
ENTRY.OWNER: Chavez Juan Carlos and Marez Yamel

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 5 5 1/2F Dirt CR: 66. Maiden Special Weight Purse 8000. FOR MAIDENS, THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: SEVENTH HOUSE was slow to begin and lagged to the first turn, rallied two then three wide on the second turn then closed with a rush to win going away. ELUSIVE GOLD stalked the pace to the second turn, came off the rail and dueled to mid stretch then could not stall the winner. ST PATRICKS SWORD chased the leaders, saved ground to the stretch, dueled late but was also bested by the winner. POCO DIABLO ROJO had no speed, swung out four wide on the second turn and made a belated run. GOTHAM'S FINALE hustled to contest the pace for five furlongs then tired. RED MEMORYS tracked the pace two wide but lacked a closing response. COLE'S DYNAMITE was four then three wide throughout and not a threat. WORK YOUR MAGIC had brief speed and gave way.

ENTRY.NAME: St Patricks Sword
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased pace, saved ground, dueled late, bested

ENTRY.NAME: Seventh House
ENTRY.COMMENT: slow to begin, rallied 2-3wide 2d turn, closed strong

ENTRY.NAME: Red Memorys
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked pace, off rail, no late rally

ENTRY.NAME: Elusive Gold
ENTRY.OWNER: Bozell Alan Gibson Elwin F and Matwiejow Donel
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace, saved ground, dueled, bested late

ENTRY.NAME: Gotham's Finale
ENTRY.COMMENT: hustled, contested pace, responded, tired stretch

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 6 5F Dirt CR: 81. Starter Allowance Purse 8000. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $4,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LOW DOSE had good speed, dueled outside of FIRE ESCAPE to the second turn but came in slightly, bumped that one, inched away to the stretch and held driving. MOSCOW LADY trailed for three eighths, swung out five wide on the far turn then made a steady late run to the line. FIRE ESCAPE dueled inside LOW DOSE to the second turn, was bumped and took up slightly then weakened. COWLITZ tracked the pace two wide for a half mile but lacked a closing response. CONFIDENCE BUILDER got outsprinted to the backstretch, was three then four wide to the stretch but could not threaten. CAL had no speed and was not a factor. The rider on FIRE ESCAPE lodged an objection against the winner LOW DOSE and following a review by the stewards, LOW DOSE was disqualified and placed third behind FIRE ESCAPE.

ENTRY.NAME: Moscow Lady
ENTRY.COMMENT: trailed, swung 5wide 2d turn, steady late rally

WINNERS_DETAILS.BREEDER: Ronald A. Hagen & Nina M. Hagen

ENTRY.NAME: dq-Low Dose
ENTRY.COMMENT: good speed, dueled, drifted in, bumped foe, dug in determinedly

ENTRY.NAME: Cowlitz
ENTRY.COMMENT: tracked pace, off rail, no rally

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 7 6F Dirt CR: 64. Claiming Purse 6500. FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Races at OR Fairs or WA Class C Tracks Not Considered in Eligiblity).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CAMDEN HIGH was well placed then responded with a strong run to collar STEEL NERVES into the second turn and drew clear under steady urging. MISS MENSA pressed the pace for a half, bid three wide on the far turn then was no threat to the winner but came on late for the place. STEEL NERVES set the pace from the rail for a half mile, could not stall the winner then weakened and could not save second. ALY'S NATION chased the pace from the rail to the stretch but failed to offer a closing bid. SHERRYS BABY also was chasing early then saved ground to no avail. FLY PATTI FLY had no speed and could not make an immpact. TED'S CANDY GIRL also had no speed and was not a factor. ARCTIC FIRE broke a bit slow, hustled up to stalk the pace for a half mile then tired. OUR GIRL ASHLEY was through early.

ENTRY.NAME: Steel Nerves
ENTRY.COMMENT: set pace, saved ground, collared, weakened

ENTRY.NAME: Camden High
ENTRY.OWNER: Dixon Chloe and Morris Michael Robert
ENTRY.COMMENT: never far back, rallied backstretch, took lead, clear driving

ENTRY.NAME: Miss Mensa
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, roused 3wide, no threat, late bid 2d

ENTRY.NAME: Aly's Nation
ENTRY.COMMENT: chased pace, saved ground, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Fly Patti Fly
ENTRY.COMMENT: no speed, asked inside, no response

ENTRY.NAME: Arctic Fire
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke step slow, hustled, tired 2d turn

RACE.FOOTNOTES: LADY BRETT dueled for the lead from the rail, responded into the stretch and held driving. RESERVOIR contested the pace with the winner, was outkicked but hustled along to again close the gap to the stretch then battled on late. DONTFORGETHESUGAR was four wide early, chased four wide to the stretch and was gaining late. SASSY EINSTEIN had no speed, was roused four wide on the second turn and closed willingly. LUTE'S DIAMOND tracked the pace three wide to the second turn but lacked the needed late response. LEAD ACTRESS settled mid pack then saved ground to no avail. CARDS N COFFEE had no speed and was not a factor. ELECTRIC ELIZABETA chased the pace for a half mile while two wide then came up emptpy. MO SUGAFOOT hustled along early, had speed for a half mile then gave out.

ENTRY.COMMENT: settled mid pack, saved ground, no bid

ENTRY.NAME: Electric Elizabeta
ENTRY.OWNER: Hurley Susan E and Haasl Ron J

ENTRY.COMMENT: contested pace, outkicked, rallied, battled, 2d best

ENTRY.NAME: Sassy Einstein
ENTRY.COMMENT: no speed, asked 4wide, steady late bid

ENTRY.NAME: Dontforgethesugar
ENTRY.COMMENT: 4wide early, chased, asked 4wide, came on late

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 9 5F Dirt CR: 67. Claiming Purse 6500. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE NEVER WON TWO RACES. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $4,000 (Races at OR Fairs or WA Class C Tracks Not Considered in Eligiblity).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: TRIBUNAL LOVE had the best speed, set all the pace and held driving. AMANDA'S BEACH BOY stalked the winner after avoiding the trouble on the first turn but could not make an impact while saving second. LET GEORGE DO IT was forced out four then five wide on the first turn, tracked to the second turn, raced three wide to the stretch then lacked the needed late response. ANOTHER STRIKE was forced out five then six wide to the backstretch, chased for three furlongs, was two wide to the stretch but came up empty. LONGFORD was forced widest of all when seven wide to the backstretch then was outsprinted and not a factor. SMOKIN KEN bore out badly on the first turn, causing all the problems then stopped after half a mile.

ENTRY.NAME: Tribunal Love
ENTRY.COMMENT: best speed, pace rail, held driving

ENTRY.NAME: Amanda's Beach Boy
ENTRY.COMMENT: stalked pace, bid 2d turn, outkicked, 2d best

ENTRY.NAME: Let George Do It
ENTRY.COMMENT: forced 4-5wide early, tracked, asked 3wide, no rally

ENTRY.NAME: Another Strike
ENTRY.COMMENT: forced 5-6wide early, chased pace, off rail, empty

RACE.RACE_TEXT: GRANTS PASS RACE 10 6 1/2F Dirt CR: 81. Claiming Purse 7200. FOR THREE YEAR OLDS AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Claiming Price $3,200. Oregon Bred Claiming Price $4,000.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: DYF pressed the pace early, moved the lead inside on the backstretch the second time, pushed away to the stretch and held driving. MISO FAST was five wide early, settled, eased in then saved ground to the stretch and was an easy second. MR BOTANICALS had no speed, raced two wide to the second turn then could only pick off rivals. RIVER ROSE tracked the pace early then saved ground to no avail. OUR EMPIRE hustled to the front early, was overtaken after three eighths and tired. SHOCKAZULU chased the pace four wide early, was asked for more two wide but came up empty. PAPAWASAROLLNSTONE stumbled badly at the start and did not recover. TUMAC MOUNTAIN was through early.

ENTRY.NAME: Dyf
ENTRY.COMMENT: pressed pace, bid rail, took lead, clear driving

ENTRY.NAME: River Rose

ENTRY.NAME: Mr Botanicals
